lowell anderson doesnt know what to do 
with his first vacation in nearly 30 years but a check for more 
than 150000 for all the time off he missed should broaden his 
choices 
it was like winning the lottery said anderson the general 
manager of carrollton municipal utilities but i pretty much knew 
it was there i figured id retire a little early 
anderson 60 earns about 56000 a year running the utilities 
in this a town of 4700 residents 70 miles northeast of kansas 
city he said he took his last vacation after he moved into the 
general managers job in 1959 
after his promotion the city council allowed him to carry his 
vacation time forward if he chose 
things just got busy and i didnt figure i could take any 
time off away from the job he said but theyre going to make 
me take some time this year i still dont know what ill do with 
it 
mayor jack mathis said the cityowned utility didnt see 
compensatory time off as a realistic option and issued a check for 
153400 throwing in a few weeks vacation 
we didnt think wed do very well without him for 2 years 
mathis said 
