<TEXT>
the supreme court today reinforced the right 
of hospitals to challenge federal regulations limiting the amount 
of money they are reimbursed for treating medicare patients 
justice anthony m kennedy wrote the unanimous opinion his 
first since joining the court feb 18 
kennedy in a case from ohio upheld the right of hospitals to 
contest unfavorable rules to a governmental agency called the 
provider reimbursement review board 
the board must hear the hospitals challenge to regulations even 
if the hospitals previously abided by the rules in their own cost 
reports kennedy said 
he said the boards required review of such challenges assures 
that medicare providers will then have the right to take their case 
to federal court if the board rules against them 
by objecting to the regulation in the first instance in 
proceedings before the board the hospitals protected their right 
to judicial review kennedy said the boards decision on 
reimbursement triggers the right of judicial review for the 
hospitals he said 
the regulation challenged by the hospitals limited their 
reimbursement for malpractice insurance premiums 
the hospitals filed cost reports for 1980 with what is known as 
a fiscal intermediary normally a private insurance company 
that accepted the governments limitations on malpractice 
reimbursement 
the hospitals then appealed to the provider reimbursement review 
board for more money but the board said it lacked authority to 
review the case because the hospitals had not challenged the 
regulation before the fiscal intermediary 
the 6th us circuit court of appeals ruled that the board acted 
properly 
kennedy said today that the appeals court ruling could deny the 
hospitals the right to a federal court hearing when they challenged 
governmental regulations 
todays decision was a victory for the bethesda hospital 
association in ohio and the deaconess hospital association of 
cincinnati 
the department of health and human services since has revised 
the formula to allow hospitals more money for malpractice costs 
the case is bethesda hospital association vs bowen 861764 
