<TEXT>
one hyperactive student is greatly helped by 
ritalin so the teacher encourages the parents of others to try it 
and they tell other parents about the happy results ritalins 
success many have led to its excess some fear its now overused 
the second story in a threeday series r is for ritalin looks 
at the increased role of a prescribed drug in the nations schools 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
something new is tucked amid the workbooks pencils and 
sandwiches in an increasing number of school backpacks each day it 
is a pill no bigger than button candy prescribed to help 
youngsters get through their multiplication tables spelling tests 
and geography lessons 
the pill is ritalin a stimulant that can assist hyperactive 
children in concentrating completing their work and controlling 
frenzied outbursts that turn classrooms to chaos 
some parents describe ritalin as a godsend 
it was like the difference between day and night said nancy 
anderson a buffalo minn mother whose daughter 11 and son 8 
take the drug the first day sarah took ritalin was the first 
time she was able to read something and understand it that night 
she told me and started crying 
i cried too 
but ritalins success may be leading to its excess as many as 1 
million children may take the drug and happy endings like the 
andersons are encouraging more doctors to prescribe it sometimes 
with less triumphant results 
many doctors say superficial diagnosis and limited followup 
have led to the medicating of the children who dont need it or 
who need additional counseling to learn how to tame the confusion 
inside their minds 
i know of several communities and school districts where 
people are excessively prescribing medication for children without 
adequately evaluating them said russell barkely director of 
psychology at the university of massachusetts medical center 
barkely said these communities to the west and north of boston 
may be seeing the children once a year and renewing the 
prescription by telephone 
the five states with the highest percapita consumption of 
ritalin utah maryland georgia minnesota and michigan have 
begun investigating its use 
georgia officials alarmed by high ritalin use in suburban 
atlanta found school personnel were urging ritalin treatment on 
parents 
we looked at what was driving the marketplace and wound up 
with the conclusion that it was the school systems said andrew 
watry executive director of georgias composite state board of 
medical examiners parents were calling us with a lot of 
anecdotal information about how their arms were twisted to take the 
medication 
lavarne parker a suburban atlanta mother believes ritalin is 
used as a chemical billy club to subdue problem students she has 
filed suit against the doctor and school officials who encouraged 
her to medicate her son 
its almost like someone said weve got a pill to give a child 
who wont do what you want him to do she said 
when susan marshalls son bradley had trouble in firstgrade 
at hingham mass she sought medical help on the schools advice 
her pediatrian prescribed ritalin 
but bradley did not improve and according to his mother 
suffered from insomnia depression and a loss of appetite mrs 
marshall finally took bradley to a neurologist who found the boys 
problems were due to a hemiparesis a limited brain injury not 
treatable by ritalin 
the marshalls are suing the pediatrician 
he simply prescribed ritalin she said we were not given 
a diagnosis 
parents like mrs marshall and mrs parker claim ritalin carries 
harsh side effects from facial tics and lost appetite to 
depression and suicide their anxieties are fed by the citizens 
commission on human rights a group supported by the church of 
scientology that opposes psychiatric treatment and is conducting a 
nationwide media campaign against ritalin 
doctors and government regulators dismiss most charges against 
ritalin as exaggerated and unsubstantiated citing some 500 
research papers that mostly agree side effects are temporary and 
minimal 
manufactured by cibageigy corp and known generically as 
methylphenidate ritalin is one in a small group of drugs used to 
treat childhood behavioral disorders and narcolepsy as a class ii 
drug it is listed along with amphetamines morphine and the 
painkiller demerol as a drug with legitimate use but high 
potential for abuse 
prescribing drugs for problem children is not new the roman 
physican galen suggested opium for overactive children in the first 
century research in the 1930s indicated that treating hyperactive 
children with stimulants usually amphetamines helped calm them 
ritalin was developed in 1955 as an alternative to amphetamines 
what has changed in the last decade is the awareness some say 
overawareness of the malady that ritalin is used to treat 
known variously over years as hyperactivity hyperkinesis and 
minimal brain disfunction the syndrome is now called attention 
deficit disorder a catchall of symptoms ranging from wild 
destructive behavior to an inability to concentrate or in 
educational jargon stay on task 
researchers say 3 to 10 percent of the nations 45 million 
schoolchildren exhibit some symptoms of add 
the american psychiatric associations diagnostic bible lists 
add symptoms such as fidgeting difficulty awaiting turns at games 
blurting out answers before being called on excessive talking and 
a penchant for losing things 
while many parents would recognize some of these noisome habits 
in their children add parents say it is the intensity of the 
behavior that separates theirs from normal children 
its the constantness of it said jean conner harrison a 
west newbury mass mother who publishes a newsletter for add 
families you are trapped in it you cant take these children 
anywhere you cant get babysitters to stay with them it is so 
emotionally tough to get through this day by day 
add is the single most researched area of child psychology some 
600 research papers on the subject were published last year add 
seminars are commonly held around the country for doctors 
educators and parents 
regional diagnostic clinics have sprung up often near research 
centers in states with high ritalin use as a result more and more 
children are being diagnosed with add and treated with medication 
critics note with alarm that ritalin production has doubled 
since 1983 but the us drug enforcement administration which 
sets production levels says that statistic sheds little light on 
how many people take a drug 
a better gauge is number of prescriptions an fda report shows 
22 million prescriptions for ritalin and related drugs were filled 
and refilled in 1986 the figure does not show the number of people 
using the drug but it does indicate an increase in use the 
number is 14 percent higher than in 1983 
thats unusual said carlene baum an fda psychologist 
the average annual increase in prescriptions for most drugs is 1 
percent 
no one is certain how many of the nations children get a daily 
dose of ritalin daniel safer a johns hopkins university child 
psychiatrist who has studied surveys at various school districts 
believes 600000 to 800000 schoolchildren receive stimulant 
medication mostly ritalin 
its been going up steadily said safer and i dont see 
it going down 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
eds this sty may be considered complete in one take a second 
take follows for those desiring more detail 
