he told parents he was playing the percentages because it had 
helped with so many cases said watry 
late last year a special study group for the georgia department 
of education recommended school personnel be warned against 
pressuring parents to seek medication and leave diagnosis and 
treatment to medical professionals 
but often these professionals are not doing a complete job 
the american academy of pediatrics recommends extensive testing 
and discussion among doctors parents and educators before 
prescribing medication 
guidelines also stress that medication is only part of the 
solution counseling therapy tutoring even special classes for 
parents are recommended 
almost everybody in the field will say you have to do more 
than give the pill said james satterfield a los angelesarea 
psychiatrist whose research found hyperactive children responded 
dramatically better to a combination of therapy and ritalin 
weve heard about pediatricians who have said heres six 
months of prescription come back when it runs out he said 
that gives a message to parents that heres this magic pill you 
dont need any other treatment 
but some question if many of those getting treatment need it 
thomas long a psychologist and director of the national center 
for family studies at the catholic university of america believes 
doctors choose medication when counseling and different parenting 
might be enough 
we have created a society that relies on medication to solve 
our problems he said the first thing you go to when you have 
a problem is some kind of pill 
