sparks from workmens torches started a 
fire at the american cultural center today damaging the building 
but causing no injuries us and fire officials said 
the fire was an accident that had absolutely no connection 
with the visit of defense secretary frank carlucci said douglas 
rose deputy director of the us information service in new delhi 
carlucci arrived in new delhi today and held two rounds of talks 
with indian officials on defense cooperation and the peace process 
in afghanistan 
the fire began on the fifth floor the buildings top story at 
about 345 pm after sparks ignited flammable gas canisters stored 
there said sk dheri the citys chief fire officer 
he said the sparks came from men repairing or cutting an 
airconditioning duct with acetylene torches 
about 150 firefighters battled the blaze for an hour at the 
american center which houses us information service offices a 
library theater meeting rooms and a media center dheri said the 
computer center on the fifth floor was safe he said 
damage was estimated at between 100000 and 300000 said 
state department spokeswoman phyllis oakley in washington rose 
said the damage was largely confined to the airconditioning room 
the building is on a main street close to the central connaught 
