interest rates on shortterm treasury 
securities rose in mondays auction to the highest levels since 
midjanuary 
the treasury department sold 64 billion in threemonth bills 
at an average discount rate of 598 percent up from 569 percent 
last week another 64 billion was sold in sixmonth bills at an 
average discount rate of 621 percent up from 60 percent last 
week 
the rates were the highest since jan 19 when threemonth bills 
sold for an identical 598 percent and sixmonth bills averaged 
637 percent 
the new discount rates understate the actual return to investors 
616 percent for threemonth bills with a 10000 bill selling 
for 984880 and 65 percent for a sixmonth bill selling for 
968610 
in a separate report the federal reserve said monday that the 
average yield for oneyear treasury bills the most popular index 
for making changes in adjustable rate mortgages was 678 percent 
last week virtually unchanged from 677 percent the previous week 
