more of the farmers home administrations 
rural development loans may be targeted to areas of high 
unemployment the agriculture department agency said monday 
fmha administrator vance l clark said a proposed change in the 
rules would direct a higher proportion of the agencys business and 
industrial loan guarantees to smaller companies where there is high 
unemployment 
the bampi program involves guarantees by fmha on loans made by 
commercial lenders to provide jobs through new or expanded 
businesses in rural areas 
as a general policy we want to gear the limited bampi loan 
funds to smaller businesses in areas where they can provide jobs 
for rural people especially displaced farmers clark said 
under the proposal loan guarantees would range from 70 percent 
to 90 percent of the loan value with the higher guarantee reserved 
for smaller loans 
a spokesman joe oneill said bampi loan guarantees range up to 
10 million per project those of up to 2 million would carry the 
90 percent guarantee 2 million to 5 million 80 percent and 5 
million to 10 million 70 percent he said 
