monday by sen daniel p moynihan dny 
shoreham should not be opened in large part because of 
the inherent problems of any possible evacuation in the event of an 
emergency simon said in a letter to moynihan jackson spokesman 
hulbert james told moynihan aides that jackson is against opening 
the 5 billion plant 
sen albert gore jr of tennessee and massachusetts gov michael 
dukakis were more cautious but both said they would support 
legislation to forbid the nuclear regulatory commission from 
licensing the plant without an emergency evacuation plan approved 
by the federal emergency management agency 
fema has said long island could not be safely evacuated without 
the cooperation of state and local officials who have refused to 
participate in such planning however the nrc changed its own 
rules last year to allow it to assume state and local officials 
would cooperate in any actual nuclear emergency 
