in one letter secret service director john r simpson vouched 
for the defendants reliability and integrity recalling when 
nofziger became the white house spokesman after president reagan 
was shot on march 30 1981 
once mr nofziger took the podium simpson said he was 
quickly aware of the rapport and trust the press had for any 
statements he made 
nofziger 63 is scheduled to be sentenced friday by us 
district judge thomas flannery for illegally lobbying on behalf of 
wedtech corp a maritime engineers union and the manufacturer of 
the air forces a10 antitank plane 
the former white house political director could receive a 
twoyear prison term and be fined as much as 10000 for each of 
the three felony convictions for lobbying excolleagues within a 
year of leaving the presidents staff 
in its filing nofzigers lawyers accused independent counsel 
james c mckay of making a vindictive and meanspirited 
request for imprisonment the defense said a prison term would 
unnecessarily add to the degradation and humiliation mr nofziger 
has already suffered as a result of his indictment and trial 
it is inconceivable that a sentence other than probation is 
appropriate under these circumstances said the sentencing memo 
filed by defense lawyers robert plotkin and e lawrence barcella 
the letters attached to the sentencing memo were from current 
and former reagan administration officials personal friends and 
political associates of nofziger who vouched for his character and 
integrity 
he has always been a man who cares more for the good of a 
cause than for personal gain wrote kemp who urged the judge to 
balance the requirements of justice with the quality of mercy 
in a threepage letter herrington urged flannery to show 
compassion and understanding for nofziger 
society has been paid by what he has gone through in this 
trial and the effect that it has had on him as an individual the 
secretary said 
lyn nofziger will never engage in this activity again in any 
way shape or form and my fear is that he will probably never 
participate in politics again and i think that will be a shame 
herrington said 
in a memo filed last week mckay said nofziger had unjustly 
enriched himself after leaving the white house in early 1982 
amassing a current net worth of 28 million 
mckay said nofziger deliberately ignored the ethics in 
government act restrictions on lobbying and showed no remorse after 
his conviction in february 
plotkin and barcella said nofzigers legal bills total 14 
million and will increase when the conviction is appealed 
the defense said nofziger does not dispute the need for fair 
clear and balanced postemployment restrictions but contended 
that if the statute were clearer mr nofziger likely would not 
be before the court for sentencing 
