police said monday they seized 
more than 58 pounds of heroin in two separate operations and 
arrested three people 
bernama the national news agency quoted superintendent adnan 
baharum of the antidrug office as saying 47 pounds were found in a 
car and house in kuala lumpur on march 25 
superintendent khalid hashim in butterworth 180 miles northwest 
of the capital said 11 pounds were seized there on sunday hidden 
in bushes 
neither official gave the source of the heroin but most 
narcotics captured in malaysia come from thailand 
police reported the kuala lumpur seizures followed the arrest of 
a 36yearold man in a car containing heroin they said a 
31yearold man was arrested in the house where more drugs were 
found and a third man was detained in a hotel 
all three will be charged under antidrug laws passed five years 
ago that carry a mandatory death sentence on conviction according 
to officials 
butterworth police had received a tip about the heroin hidden 
there and had the area under surveillance but no one came to 
collect it and there were no arrests police said 
idris ibrahim of the national association for the prevention of 
drug abuse said sunday that 62 drug traffickers have been executed 
this year and 109 are on death row while their appeals are 
considered 
