martin luther king jr and that dream lives said the rev ben 
chavis 
pierce shot to death at his home on march 26 in what 
authorities said was a domestic dispute was running for a superior 
court judgeship many lumbees and blacks in the county say they are 
discriminated against and that they are not represented adequately 
in local political offices the countys population is 37 percent 
indian 37 percent white and 26 percent black 
in albany ny the rev al sharpton was arrested for refusing 
to move out of a road outside the state capitol three people were 
arrested with sharpton and 10 others including folk singer pete 
seeger were detained after refusing to leave a service road 
their rally was called to protest state handling of the case of 
tawana brawley a black teenager who claims she was assaulted by a 
group of white men sharpton had threatened to shut down state 
agencies on the anniversary of kings death sharpton and others 
among miss brawleys advisers have refused to let her cooperate 
with the state investigation 
about 200 people representing various religious groups prayed 
shouted and sang outside the mobil oil corp headquarters in 
manhattan in an antiapartheid demonstration coinciding with the 
king observances the group urged mobil to stop doing business in 
south africa 
