ronald hunter president of the erie county ny chapter of the 
sclc if dr king were alive today hed be very disillusioned 
some things are worse than 20 years ago he said in 
addition to high unemployment there are more school dropouts high 
drug and alcohol abuse more teenage pregnancy 
the civil rights movement is almost at a standstill and many 
young blacks lack the perspective of older civil rights workers 
said daniel r acker president of the buffalo ny chapter of 
the national association for the advancement of colored people 
they never knew the humiliation of jim crowism of colored 
only drinking fountains and being forced to ride in the back of 
the bus acker said 
