<TEXT>
a former wedtech corp executive testified 
monday that the scandalplagued defense contractor tried 
unsuccessfully to sell military equipment to iran iraq and saudi 
arabia 
the negotiations to sell bridge pontoons and other supplies 
eventually fell through with all three nations said former wedtech 
vice chairman mario moreno 
moreno in his 14th day of testimony at the racketeering trial 
of rep mario biaggi dny and six others was questioned by 
defense attorneys about wedtechs middle east dealings 
the jury was not present during questioning on that topic and 
