<TEXT>
with sincere emotion i read your most attentive letter 
addressed to me dated march 23 delivered by cirilo mcsween in 
which you expressed your moral concern for the political and 
economic living conditions of the panamanian people your concern 
for the crisis which has provoked great suffering and your appeal 
to me to persist in seeking peace and to put an end to this crisis 
you expressed your anxiety to do whatever is possible to help 
alleviate the suffering and that we should act immediately 
your reputation as a great moral authority obligates me to give 
consideration and pay attention to your appeal so that we may work 
together for the peace and unification of my country in this 
sense i manifest that it has always been one of the objectives of 
the defense force and mine to try to keep social peace for the 
panamanian brothers and sisters and the foreigners that reside in 
our country our doctrine of national security is inspired in the 
ideals of social justice and not of military concepts 
i am sure that you are aware of the deep internal and external 
aspects of the political and economic situation now they have been 
destabalizing our consitutional panamanian institutions so as to 
have a country that is weak and ruined so it becomes an easy prey 
for the dictates of foreign forces i am sure that you know the 
details of the amalgam between professional panamanian politicians 
that are now dressed in sheepskin and the legislative and 
executive sectors of the united states of america who have 
translated an open and barefaced intervention into the internal 
affairs of panama with the final proposition that they do not give 
compliment to the covenant of the torrijoscarter treaty of 1977 
no panamanian with a firm nationalistic and patriotic sentiment 
would ever accept that the solution of internal problems of the 
republic of panama be dictated from washington dc 
consequently i find it unnecesary to repeat this answer to your 
letter with more details in the wheel of the panamanian crisis 
there is something that has awakened my curiosity and come to my 
attention how is it possible that the reagans administration who 
has publicly made gala of great love for god and have profound 
religious sentiment has campaigned terrible economic sanctions that 
have been imposed on the panamanian people causing the kind of 
suffering that you feel sincerely inhuman causing the threat of 
brutal military forces the sabotage the psychological war against 
a materially small and weak country but a dignified coungry just 
like panama is 
manuel solis palma is the actual head of state of panama by 
constitutional decision of the legislative assembly it is 
recognized by the supreme court of justice he has recently called 
for a sincere national dialogue between all the sectors of the 
panamanian society with the purpose of a specific solution for the 
democracy of our country with upcoming celebration of free and 
open elections of may 1989 
the defense forces support this cause by the panamanian chief of 
state and at the same time reject any imposition and any political 
and economic program that will be dictated from washington dc 
the word perpetuity has been historically imposed on panama 
by the unied states of america in the different canal treaties 
since 1903 nevertheless i assure you that those words do not 
form a part of my personal vocabulary nor of my honor in the 
military my duration as commander and chief of the defense forces 
is governed by the panamanian constitution and law of the defense 
forces 
you can do a lot to help by eliminating one of the principal 
causes of the suffering of many panamanians in other words the 
foreign intervention you may contribute by your knowledgeable 
advice and create by mutual communition the harmony and the 
material peace between all panamanians without discrimination of 
any class 
with my deepest respect for you i shall be at your disposition 
to speak with you more deeply about this theme whenever you are 
available 
attentively 
 
ps i have been lied about i have been villafied i have been 
humiliated internationally 
i consider myself to have been persecuted by illegal actions by 
socalled justice by political interests of your nation 
i as a christian before you denounce this untrue because how 
is it possible that nation as powerful should employ the services 
of journalistic misinformation the threat of death bdfore one of 
gods children such as i consider to be at the present time in 
this struggle 
this is my testimony reverend jackson before the divine and 
eternal laws of the allpowerful god 
i feel rich in faith and find my situation in isaiah 45 with 
all humility and reverence 
