the arizona senate convicted gov evan 
mecham on monday of attempting to thwart a deaththreat 
investigation and misusing funds making him the first us 
governor impeached and removed from office in 59 years 
acting gov rose mofford a democrat became governor the moment 
the gavel fell to close the 219 vote to convict on the first 
