sen albert gore jr is seeking to establish 
his differences with the middle east policies of democratic 
presidential rivals jesse jackson and michael dukakis in the weeks 
before the crucial new york primary 
nowhere does the issue of us policy toward israel and the 
middle east loom larger than in new york where jews cast 22 
percent of the votes in 1984 the state holds its presidential 
primaries april 19 
many jews remain wary of jackson who on a 1979 trip to the 
middle east embraced palestinian liberation organization leader 
yassar arafat and called israel a state of oppressors he also 
described the plo as not merely a terrorist organization even 
though it has engaged in some terrorist acts it is a government in 
exile 
