worldclass barcrawler best friend 
keifer sutherland simply is allagash phoebe cates is blinking 
perfection as amanda who is more an idea than a character in the 
movie as in the book tracy pollan plays tads downtoearth cousin 
who represents jamies salvation 
jason robards steals scenes as an alcoholic hasbeen editor at 
jamies magazine his son sam has a small part as a clubgoer 
swoosie kurtz is the goodhearted coworker who tries to help 
jamie but has her own agenda and frances sternhagen as clara 
jamies boss turns the villainess of the book into a palpable 
visage of authoritarian disapproval even while welling up with 
tears when forced to fire jamie for incompetence 
dianne wiest as jamies beloved dying mother is swathed in an 
almost christlike glow for her brief but pivotal role in 
flashback on her death bed she earnestly asks him what its like 
being a young man does he sleep with many girls does he like it 
is it fun since the entire story turns on the believability of 
their love for each other these moments are especially demanding 
on actors and director and they work wonderfully 
the movie starts just like the book and ends just like the book 
