michael murray and the organ of the cathedral of st john the 
divine telarc 
 
michael murrays program is designed to show off some of the 
special qualities of the organ of the episcopal cathedral of st 
john the divine in new york city one of the worlds largest 
churches the organ is likewise immense with 143 ranks of pipes 
and murray gives pride of place to some of the solo stops for which 
organ builder em skinner was famous 
where else but perhaps in this recording of the emperors 
fanfare by padre antonio soler will your hear a tuba major a 
cornopean and an ophicleide in full cry 
the cathedrals distinctive herald trumpet mounted under the 
west rose window a good 500 feet from the rest of the organ is 
also shown off in john dunstables agincourt hymn and henry 
purcells trumpet tune 
still the recording can only hint at the feeling of being 
within that enormous unfinished space 200 feet wide and 12 stories 
high 
by robert barr associated press writer 
