<TEXT>
how does your garden grow 
not with silver bells and cockle shells despite the nursery 
rhyme 
it takes knowhow to be a successful gardener and correcting 
common misconceptions can make the difference according to plant 
care experts jack peters and jim knauss 
the amateur gardener can increase the health potential of plants 
throughout the year by knowing more about ageold assumptions that 
arent necessarily so they say 
in most of these cases the amateur gardener tends to err on 
the side of excess says knauss who is manager of technical and 
analytical information services at wr grace amp cos peter plants 
food division the healthiest plants are those that have the 
benefit of simple consistent attention 
one misconception he says is to always keep the soil surface 
moist a common practice says knauss but one that can keep 
plants and gardens from getting the air they need the telltale 
area is deeper within the soil before bringing out the watering 
can put a finger about 12 inches beneath the soil to test the 
dryness when watering the liquid should go far beyond just 
the surface making sure the roots are fully moistened 
another common idea to reassess is that selecting plants with 
the lushest greenest foliage at the garden center will ensure easy 
care survival says peters producer manager for peters plant food 
people tend to feel that a lush healthy plant will remain 
that way with a minimum of care and attention he says what 
they dont see is the extent of the care that plant had been 
receiving at the greenhouse or nursery that particular plant may 
despite its looks be quite difficult to maintain and keep healthy 
knowing about the variety and maintaining consistent 
environments are the important determinants of long plant health 
not simply the original plants appearance 
</TEXT>
