<TEXT>
a coldframe can extend your gardening efforts both in early 
spring and in fall it is useful to condition young seedlings that 
were sown indoors for later planting outdoors 
a coldframe can be built as a leanto against the house by 
covering the frame with a storm sash or a similar type of window 
the framework of the bed can be made of wood or concrete for wood 
the boards should be 2 inches thick 
the front of the frame should face south and should be at least 
2 inches below ground level the back portion of the frame should 
be 6 inches higher than the front with a slope of about 1 inch per 
foot bank up the soil on the outside of the frame to help conserve 
heat 
during spring and fall when the frame is in use lift the sash 
on warm days but be sure to close it on cool nights to conserve 
moisture and heat inside 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
